==English==

===Etymology===

From the Latin ''perspicuus'', in turn from ''perspicere'', to see through something.

===Adjective===
'''Perspicuous'''
# Clearly expressed, easy to understand. Used in [[logic]] to describe a language or [[notation]], such as that of formal propositional calculus, where the process of [[inference]] from [[premise|premises]] to [[conclusion]] is explicitly laid out.